1 Usage
*******

Start by creating an env file in ‘setenv-file-dir’ (by default,
‘~/.env/’).  For example, create this file in ‘~/.env/foo’:

     FOO=~/foo
     BAR=$FOO/bar
     ОФИС=ДОМ
     BAZ=nosubst:FOO$BAR

   Note that you can customize ‘setenv-file-dir’ if you like, like this:

     (setq setenv-file-dir
           (expand-file-name "~/another/path/"))

